{"id": "duc04-testb-38:0#1", "contents": "The meeting in Damascus took place amidst rising tensions between Syria and Turkey, with Turkey massing forces near the border and threatening to eradicate Kurdish rebel bases in Syria. Turkish jets had also buzzed the Syrian frontier in a show of force. Mubarak had previously visited Riyadh to secure King Fahd of Saudi Arabia's backing for his mediation efforts. Egypt frequently plays a mediating role in Arab and Muslim disputes, and Mubarak expressed his commitment to containing the tension and stopping military threats."}
